<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Donates 40 Trucks to Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- China has donated a total of 40
tipper trucks to Uganda and the hand-over ceremony took place
Thursday morning near the Mokono town, 20 kms east of the capital
Kampala.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Uganda Song Zengshou and Ugandan
Minister of State for Works, Housing and Communications Hon.
Andruale Awuzu attended the function on behalf of their
respective governments.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Song said these tippers had been transported here
in response to the request of the Ugandan government. It
demonstrated the goodwill of the Chinese government and its
people to the government and people of Uganda.
</P>
<P>
China and Uganda are facing the similar problem of economic
development, he added, hoping that Uganda, under the leadership
of President Yoweri Museveni, makes more remarkable achievements.
</P>
<P>
Awuzu said the trucks, to be distributed to every district of
Uganda, will be used in garbage collection and will help create a
cleaner environment.
</P>
<P>
He thanked the Chinese government for the assistance extended
to his country.
</P>
<P>
The 40 brand-new trucks, made by China's First Automobile
Manufacturing Corporation, were transported here more than a
month ago to undergo adjustment and various tests before being
officially handed over to Ugandans.
</P>
<P>
More than 70 local officials representing every district of
Uganda were present at the function. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
