<HEADLINE> Pak Patience Should Not Be Considered Weakness: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif said Thursday that Pakistan does not want to react in haste
and hurry to India's nuclear tests but its "patience should not be
considered as its weakness."
</P>
<P>
"We do not want to react in haste and hurry and any decision
taken in this regard will be taken in the best national interest,"
Sharif told editors of national dailies and periodicals who called
on him Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan has shown restraint despite India's provocative and
irresponsible actions, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, the prime minister made it clear that "Pakistan's
patience should not be considered as its weakness."
</P>
<P>
"We want to make the world believe that we are a responsible
nation," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said Pakistan would defend its geographical and ideological
frontiers at any cost, adding his government is closely watching
the whole situation.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that Pakistan has the capability to meet any
challenge and give a matching response to any aggression.
</P>
<P>
He said Pakistan expects the international community especially
the major powers to exert pressure on India to stop adventurism.
</P>
</TEXT>
