<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 5 Lebanese Wounded in Israeli Air Raid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Five Lebanese were wounded Thursday
in an Israeli air raid on Lebanon's eastern Province of Bekaa
Valley, the country's independent Central News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The five, including three civilians and two guerrillas of the
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, were wounded when Israeli warplanes
swooped down on a mountainous area in the western Bekaa Valley.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli jets fired a total of four air-to-surface missiles
at their suspected Hezbollah targets, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The air raid, the 41st into Lebanon so far this year, also
destroyed some crops and caused fire, it added.
</P>
<P>
The attack brought to 31 the number of Lebanese civilians
wounded in Israeli military operations against Hezbollah
guerrillas since the start of this year. Nine civilians were
killed.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah, or Party of God, is leading a guerrilla war trying
to dislodge some 2,000 Israeli occupying forces and its 2,500
South Lebanese Army allies from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a 1,200-square-kilometer border strip in south
Lebanon in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its northern
areas from Lebanese guerrilla cross-border attack. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980522.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Red-Light Running Leads to More Deaths </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Red-light runners cause 250,000
traffic crashes a year, causing an increased number of deaths in
the United States, said a new study.
</P>
<P>
The number of fatal crashes involving red-light running
increased 15 percent, from 702 in 1992 to 809 in 1996, the
Insurance Institute for Highway Safety said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
From 1992 through 1996, there were 3,753 crashes caused by a
motorist running a red light -- about 3 percent of all fatal
crashes. Those crashes killed 4,238 people, said study researcher
Richard Retting.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Transportation Secretary Rodney Slater announced a
nationwide campaign to educate drivers about the problem and
install more cameras at intersections to catch offenders.
</P>
<P>
Researchers at the Insurance Institute based the study on two
government databases, including the Fatality Analysis Reporting
System containing details of nearly all police-reported fatal
motor vehicle crashes in the United States.
</P>
<P>
About a quarter of the 1 million traffic crashes at signals
each year involve running red lights. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980522.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Welcomes Suharto's Decision to Stand Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) Thursday
welcomed the resignation of former Indonesian President Suharto
and urged its successor President Jusuf Habibie to create a
government accountable to its people.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Suharto, who had been Indonesia's top
leader for 32 years, agreed to give up his presidency early
Thursday amid increasing pressures for him to resign.
</P>
<P>
British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook, whose country is the
current EU president, said in a statement issued on behalf of the
15-nation bloc, "We welcomes former President Suharto's decision
to stand down."
</P>
<P>
"This provides an opportunity for the process of political
reform in Indonesia to be taken forward. We urge President Habibie
to put in place democratic structures and institutions that create
a government that is accountable to the people of Indonesia," Cook
said.
</P>
<P>
Cook also expressed the hope that "Indonesia will be able to
see through a rapid and orderly transition." 
</P>
</TEXT>
