<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Communist Parties to Discuss New Strategy in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of communist parties
from 50 countries will meet in the Greek capital of Athens to
discuss how to better coordinate their action in the current
world.
</P>
<P>
The three-day meeting, "The Communist Party and Current
Conditions," is being organized by the Communist Party of Greece
(KKE) and will be held on the occasion of the 80th anniversary of
the founding of the KKE and the 150th anniversary of the
publication of the Communist Manifesto, the semi-official Athens
News Agency (ANA) reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Participants will exchange their views on the major
contemporary problems faced by the working class.
</P>
<P>
The KKE, the third strongest party in Greece, has organized two
such international meetings in 1996 and 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
