<HEADLINE> Jordan Reiterates Support for Palestinians in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Jordan Thursday reiterated its
support to the establishment of an independent Palestinian state.
</P>
<P>
Jordan's Senate Speaker Zeid Rifai told reporters here that the
kingdom sticks to a "firm and principled" stand in supporting the
Palestinians, especially at a time when the Palestinian-Israeli
peace talks are stalled due to Israeli intransigency.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks after meeting a delegation from the
Palestinian Council that arrived here Tuesday on a three-day
official visit.
</P>
<P>
Jordan supports the Palestinians in their pursuit to realize
their national rights, the foremost of which is the establishment
of an independent Palestinian state on their national soil, he
said.
</P>
<P>
In a show of support to the Palestinians, the kingdom's
leadership always presses Israel to take "positive and
constructive" steps to restart peace talks with the Palestinians
and commit itself to the agreements it signed before, said Rifai.
</P>
<P>
"Israel's continuous intransigent policy will aggravate the
intense situation in the region," he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Rifai expressed satisfaction over the
"distinguished, brotherly" ties linking Jordan and the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA).
</P>
<P>
The delegation is here to discuss with Jordanian officials the
political situation on the Palestinian-Israeli track and enhance
bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian-Israeli peace negotiation has been deadlocked
since March last year due to Israeli government's hardline
policy. The PNA has set May 1999 as the time to declare an
independent Palestinian state, but Israel has warned the
Palestinians not to take unilateral actions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
