<HEADLINE> Security Council Authorizes IPTF Strength Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Security Council
Thursday unanimously adopted a resolution authorizing an increase
of 30 posts in the strength of the International Police Task Force
(IPTF) stationed in Bosnia and Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council made the decision after it reviewed the
U.N. secretary-general's latest report on the developments in the
area.
</P>
<P>
The council encouraged member states to intensify their efforts
to provide, on a voluntary-funded basis and in coordination with
the IPTF, training, equipment and related assistance for local
police forces in Bosnia and Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
The IPTF was established in accordance with the General
Framework Agreement for Peace in Bosnia and Herzegovina reached in
1995. 
</P>
