<HEADLINE> Romanian President to Visit Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu will pay an official visit to Canada from May 24 to
30 at the invitation of Governor General Romeo Leblanc.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien made the announcement
Thursday in a news release from his office.
</P>
<P>
"I welcome President Constantinescu's visit to Canada, and I
look forward to discussing ways of increasing and diversifying our
economic and trade relations," Chretien said.
</P>
<P>
"I am also pleased to note that a delegation of Romanian
business people will be in Canada exploring new trade and
investment opportunities during the president's visit," he added.
</P>
<P>
Here in Ottawa, Constantinescu is scheduled to meet with
Chretien, Deputy Prime Minister Herb Gray, the governor general,
the speakers of the Senate and the House of Commons.
</P>
<P>
He will also travel to Canada's largest city of Toronto, and
the cities of Montreal, Quebec and Edmonton, according to the
release. 
</P>
</TEXT>
