<HEADLINE> Jordan Telecom to Join FLAG Subsea Fiber Cable System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- FLAG (Fiberoptic Link Around the
Globe), the world's longest undersea fiber cable system, is to be
extended into Jordan following the formal approval of the board of
Jordan Telecommunications Company (JTC).
</P>
<P>
FLAG is a 27,300 kilometer cable which runs from the UK to
Japan via the Atlantic Ocean, the Mediterranean Sea, the Red Sea,
the Indian Ocean and the South China Sea.
</P>
<P>
Following the decision of the board, JTC and FLAG Limited, the
owner and operator the FLAG cable system, have now entered the
final phase of negotiations, FLAG Telecom announced here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, a 175 kilometer link will be built from a
branching unit in the FLAG cable from under the Red Sea to the
Jordanian port of Aqaba.
</P>
<P>
The landing Point Station will be operated by JTC and is
expected to enter service in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Andres B. Bande, chairman of FLAG Telecom, said, "We are
delighted that the Board of JTC has chosen FLAG to deliver
broadband communications services, and we look forward to a formal
signing of the Landing Party Agreement very shortly." 
</P>
</TEXT>
