<HEADLINE> Yemen, Ethiopia Consolidate Economic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni ambassador to Ethiopia
Marwan A. Noman said on Thursday the economic relations between
Yemen and Ethiopia have shown a marked growth over the past
years.
</P>
<P>
In a press conference held here on the eighth anniversary of
the unification of north and south yemen, the ambassador said
Yemen has recently agreed to supply butane to Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
He told journalists that another agreement enabling Yemen to
supply petroleum and petrol products to Ethiopia is expected to
be signed between the two countries shortly.
</P>
<P>
Yemen attaches great significance to its cooperation with
Ethiopia, the ambassador said, adding that Ethiopia and Yemen
have wider opportunities for cooperation particularly in the
fields in trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia imports petroleum and petorl products directly from
abroad after the closure of Asseb refinery last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
