<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNEP Urged to Undertake Reform Under Nairobi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 21 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese delegate Thursday said
that the United Nations Environment Program (UNEP) must undertake
reform guided by the Nairobi Declaration in order to effectively
fulfill its mandate.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the on-going fifth special session of the UNEP
Governing Council, the Chinese delegation member said that a
strong UNEP would make greater contributions to the global cause
of environment and development.
</P>
<P>
He proposed at the three-day meeting that a science and
technology advisor committee should be established to make
advisory recommendations to UNEP on emerging environmental
issues.
</P>
<P>
The committee consisting of experts of various disciplines
related to the environment will provide scientific basis for the
decision making of UNEP, he added.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the UNEP Secretariat, he noted that the
Secretariat should undertake effective reform and the Chinese
government is of the view that the reform of UNEP Secretariat is
one of the key steps in UNEP's reform and revitalization.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that as the leading environmental authority
within the United Nations, UNEP must have the power to formulate
global environmental agenda, make recommendations on global
environmental policies, organize and coordinate global
environmental activities.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of the regional offices, the Chinese delegation
noted, they should play an important role in the formulation and
implementation of UNEP programs.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government supports the Task Force chaired by UNEP
Executive Director Klaus Topfer on the reform in the field of
environment and human settlement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
