<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances Kiev Heating Needs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved Thursday
a 200 million U.S. dollar loan to help finance the Kiev District
Heating Improvement Project in Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
This project will replace and increase heat production capacity
to better meet existing and expected future demand of district
heating, introduce modern technologies and materials to extend the
life of the Kiev district heating system.
</P>
<P>
Total project cost, including contingencies, is some 308.9
million dollars. Apart from the World Bank loan, the European Bank
for Reconstruction and Development will provide 40 million dollars
equivalent, Kievenergo will contribute 54.2 million dollars and
the Kiev Municipal District Heating Company 14.7 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Since Ukraine joined the World Bank in 1992, commitments total
over 2.2 billion dollars for 14 projects, including 2 guarantees.
</P>
</TEXT>
