<HEADLINE> London Stocks End Higher for Third Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- British shares on the London market
closed higher Thursday for a third session in a row, lifted by
rallies in Asian markets and Indonesian President Suharto's
resignation.
</P>
<P>
The UK's FTSE-100 index of leading shares managed its third
consecutive advance and finished the day up 28.2 points or 0.48
percent up at 5,935.6, as takeover talk and an improved outlook
for interest rates underpinned shares.
</P>
<P>
Weaker-than-expected UK retail sales figures and comments from
Bank of England officials convinced investors that UK interest
rates have peaked.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, exporters benefited from a weak sterling which fell
to its lowest in 6.5 months at 2.8625 marks.
</P>
<P>
Stock markets in Germany and France were closed Thursday for
the Ascension Day holiday and will reopen Friday.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, the DAX-30 index in Frankurt gained 2.27 percent
to close at a record 5,510.98 while the CAC-40 index index in
Paris closed up 67.08 points, or 1.69 percent, at 4,047.92.
</P>
</TEXT>
