<HEADLINE> Fuzhou Opens Modern Chinese Navy Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Modern Chinese Navy Museum
opened to the public today in this capital of east China's Fujian
Province.
</P>
<P>
The museum is located in the Mawei Economic and Technological
Development Zone, the birthplace of the modern Chinese navy and
shipbuilding industry. The zone will invest a total of 20 million
yuan in the museum's construction, which is to be completed by the
year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Built at a cost of seven million yuan, the first section of the
museum is a three-story exhibition building, designed to house
historical relics, photos and replicas, illustrating the history
and development of the modern Chinese navy and shipbuilding
industry.
</P>
<P>
The second section is to be equipped with the latest high-tech
facilities to give visitors a vivid impression of naval battles in
modern Chinese history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
