<HEADLINE> Latvia Hopes to Strengthen Military Cooperation with Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Latvian Defense Minister Talavs
Jundzis said in the Latvian capital of Riga Friday that he hopes
his country and Russia can strengthen their military cooperation,
reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
He told the Interfax News Agency that the two armed services
could begin their cooperation by jointly looking for and
destroying mines in the Baltic Sea.
</P>
<P>
Those mines were laid during World War I and II by Soviet Union
troops stationed in Latvia at that time.
</P>
<P>
The minister said Latvia has started working with Germany,
Denmark and Sweden.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Latvia hopes to normalize its relations with
Russia, saying joint military actions will help the two establish
a relationship of mutual trust. 
</P>
</TEXT>
