<HEADLINE> Demirel: Turkey Wishes to Buy Weapons from Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel
said on Thursday evening that Turkey would like to cooperate with
Ukraine in the defense industry.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a joint press conference with Ukrainian President
Leonid Kuchma, Demirel said that within the next 30 years, Turkey
will appropriate 150 billion U.S. dollars for military equipment
and technology.
</P>
<P>
There are broad future prospects for military cooperation with
Ukraine, he said.
</P>
<P>
Demirel arrived in Kiev Thursday for a three-day official
visit. He met his Ukrainian counterpart Kuchma and they signed a
series of bilateral agreements.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma said that Ukraine is ready to expand its military
cooperation with Turkey and that Turkey's military appropriations
will provide the fuel for the cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A Ukrainian government source said that Ukraine had proposed a
deal of 2 billion U.S. dollars for T-84 tanks.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma also indicated that Ukraine can help Turkey in building
water facilities and power stations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
