<HEADLINE> Guangdong Puts Forth New Development Framework </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province has put forth a new development framework in order to
achieve sustained economic growth in the future.
</P>
<P>
Li Changchun, secretary of the Guangdong Provincial Committee
of the Communist Party of China (CPC), today announced the
province's "three strategies" and "four advantages" for its future
development.
</P>
<P>
He explained the "three strategies" by saying that
Guangdong must give full play to its foreign-oriented economy,
develop its high-technology sector at a rapid speed and implement
the sustainable development strategy.
</P>
<P>
In order to reach its target, the province must vigorously
develop the "four advantages", namely, the advantage of the
socialist market economy, the industrial advantage, the opening
advantage and the technology advantage, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech at the Eighth Guangdong Provincial CPC
Congress, Li said that the next five years will be an important
period for the province's modernization drive, and Guangdong must
speed up its economic restructuring and upgrade its products to
catch up with the developments of the international economy.
enditem
