<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Appeals to Coal Miners to Cooperate With Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin on
Friday called upon coal miners to cooperate with the government in
solving the current crisis in the coal industry.
</P>
<P>
In a routine speech over the radio, Yeltsin said the government
is taking all measures possible to solve the coal industry
crisis. He believes the government and the coal miners can finally
solve all the problems.
</P>
<P>
But he stressed that in dealing with problems in the coal
industry, the government can not borrow money from other accounts
in the budget and can not increase the circulation of the currency.
</P>
<P>
He told people that the government has taken a lead in reducing
half of its agencies and that the government, parliament and
presidential office will cut their administrative spending by 25
percent.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the difficulties of the coal industry are
tremendous and can not be solved with one stroke, Yeltsin
expressed the hope that the coal miners will not take any action
that will exacerbate the situation.
</P>
<P>
Coal miners in the Pechora, Kuzbas, Kmerovo and Rostov coal
basins have staged strikes from May 13 since they have not been
paid for a long time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
