<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Shanghai Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The stock market in this east
China metropolis, one of the two stock markets in China, has been
in a state of adjustment, with total volumes decreasing sharply this
week.
</P>
<P>
The Composite Stock Index on the exchange finished at 1,375.82
today, up 0.57 percent over last week and a new record in
recent weeks.
</P>
<P>
The SSR-30 index, based on 30 blue chips that are selected from
more than 200 A-shares for domestic investors on the Shanghai
Stock Exchange, closed at 3,793.67, down 1.25 percent over
last week.
</P>
<P>
This week's total turnover was 30.0778 billion yuan (over three
billion US dollars), a decrease of 12.309 billion yuan over last
week.
</P>
<P>
The B-share market is also in an adjustment phase, with the
index closing at 48.09 today, down five percent over last week. The
total turnover of the B-share market reached 233 million US
dollars, about the same amount as last week's figure.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai market did not sustain the big-volume growth
of last week, with a total turnover of 2.194 billion yuan, a
decrease of 1.617 billion yuan over last week.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai bond market is active this week, with a total
turnover of 51.417 billion yuan, an increase of 11.1 billion yuan
over last week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
