<DOCNO> XIE19980522.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungary's Foreign Debt Drops Steadily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Hungary's Foreign Debt is
continuing on a downward trend with the net external debt
currently standing at 8.5 billion U.S. dollars from 18.2 billion
in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Gross foreign debt dropped to 20 billion dollars now compared
with 27.8 billion in 1994.
</P>
<P>
State direct debts declined to 3.5 billion dollars as opposed
to 15.1 billion in 1994, a major change in debt structure.
</P>
<P>
Hungary was once plagued with a net per capita foreign debt
ranking the highest in Europe.
</P>
<P>
The about face is due in some part to earnings from
privatization and increased exports thanks to upgrading and
competitiveness. 
</P>
