<HEADLINE> France Says Israel Rejection of Proposal Not Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 22 (Xinhua) -- France said on Friday that the
rejection by Israel of a Franco-Egyptian proposal on holding an
international conference on Middle East peace process does not
seem to be the final stand of the Israeli government.
</P>
<P>
"One should not conclude too quickly," said French Foreign
Ministry spokesman Yves Doutriaux, who described the declaration
by Israel in rejecting the proposal as "interesting."
</P>
<P>
