proposal, presented Monday by President Jacques Chirac and
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak, who called on all parties
resolved for peace in the Middle East to take part in such a
conference.
</P>
<P>
Israel Friday rejected the proposal, saying that it would not
participate in a conference to which the main parties involved in
the Middle East peace process are not even invited.
</P>
<P>
But Israel said it wishes to hold "direct negotiations" with
the Palestinians, Syria and Lebanon. 
</P>
