<HEADLINE> More Firms in China Have "Green Passports" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- With the Sino-American Shanghai
Squibb Pharmaceuticals Ltd (SASS) receiving the ISO 14001
certificate, the number of companies with "green passports" in
China has reached 35.
</P>
<P>
The SASS is the first pharmaceutical firm in China to
pass the environmental management examination.
</P>
<P>
The ISO 14001 certificate, regarded as the "green passport" to
the international market in the next century, is issued to
enterprises that strictly control pollution and use resources
efficiently in production.
</P>
<P>
China established a national committee to promote
international environmental management standards ISO 14001 after
introducing them from the International Standards Organization
(ISO) in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Most of the Chinese enterprises receiving the ISO 14001
certificates are in the electronic, chemical, metallurgical and
engineering industries.
</P>
<P>
Environmentalists here say that the promotion of the standards
will help the country's economic activities comply with the
requirements of environmental protection, and is of great
significance for pollution control and energy saving.
</P>
<P>
China's first auditors of environmental management standards
have passed the required examinations and are now working at their
posts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
