<HEADLINE> HK's April Foreign Currency Assets Remains 3rd Largest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary Authority
(HKMA) announced Friday that the official foreign currency assets
of Hong Kong were 96.2 billion U.S. dollars at the end of April
1998, 600 million U.S. dollars less than that at the end of last
month.
</P>
<P>
In terms of foreign currency reserves ranking, Hong Kong
remains the third largest in the world, after Japan and China's
mainland.
</P>
<P>
The foreign currency assets are held in the Exchange Fund and
the Land Fund. As at the end of April, the foreign currency assets
held in the Exchange Fund were 77.7 billion U.S. dollars compared
with 78.5 billion U.S. dollars at the end of March and the Land
Fund were 18.5 billion U.S. dollars compared with 18.3 billion
U.S. dollars at the end of March.
</P>
<P>
The fall in foreign currency assets held in the Exchange Fund
can be attributed to withdrawals of fiscal reserves to meet
government operational needs, said a spokesman for the HKMA.
</P>
</TEXT>
