<HEADLINE> Guangdong's Economy Leaps to Higher Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The economy of south China's
Guangdong Province has made great strides over the past five
years, thanks to its economic restructuring and readjustment
measures.
</P>
<P>
Li Changchun, secretary of the Guangdong Provincial Committee
of the Communist Party of China (CPC), made the remarks at the
Eighth Guangdong Provincial CPC Congress, that opened today in this
capital of the province.
</P>
<P>
Li, also member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee, said the past five years has seen the fastest development
ever in the province's transportation, energy and communication
sectors, and the province has basically wiped out barriers that
hinder economic development.
</P>
<P>
The fundamental status of agriculture has been consolidated in
the province, he noted, adding that grain production has
increased successively for four years.
</P>
<P>
Referring to industrial development, Li said the province
has made remarkable achievements in developing pillar industries,
conglomerates and brand-name products, and the volume of
industrial growth has increased by an average of 22.3 percent each
year.
</P>
<P>
The export-oriented sector has increased rapidly, he said. The
export volume and actual use of foreign funds rose by 31.6 percent
and 23.9 percent, respectively, on average annually in the past
five years.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the province's industrial structure is becoming
more rational. The average annual growth of the GDP in the
province reached 15.4 percent in the past five years, while the
per capita GDP surpassed 10,000 yuan (about 1,200 US dollars) each
year, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
