<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets Thai Crown Prince </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Sino-Thai relations have become a
model for ties between countries with different social systems,
Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao said here today.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with Thai Crown Prince H.R.H. Maha Vajiralongkorn,
Hu said that the visitor's China tour, after a break of six years,
has brought the deep feelings the Thai people have for the Chinese
people, and it will serve to further deepen their mutual
understanding and traditional friendship.
</P>
<P>
He described bilateral relations as having developed in a
smooth way since the establishment of diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
The crown prince said the frequent exchange of visits and close
relations between leaders of the two nations have served as
important guarantees for the smooth development of bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
He has long been interested in China's economic development, he
said, adding that he appreciated the achievements China has scored
in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Hu briefed the visitor on China's reform and opening-up drive,
and its economic development. China is concerned about and
sympathizes with the Thai people suffering from difficulties
brought about by the Asian financial crisis, he added.
</P>
<P>
The crown prince expressed thanks for this.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the meeting, Hu hosted a ceremony to honor the Thai
visitor.
</P>
<P>
Among those at the meeting were Tumor Dawamat, vice-chairman of
the Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress, and
Zhang Kehui, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference.
</P>
<P>
Crown Prince Vajiralongkorn, as a representative of King
Bhumibol Adulyadej, arrived here this afternoon by a special plane
for a week-long official visit to China.
</P>
<P>
Besides Beijing, the crown prince will also visit Huangshan,
Nanjing, Yangzhou and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
