<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Thai Crown Prince </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The long-standing smooth
development of Sino-Thai relations could not have been achieved
without the close attention paid by the two countries' leaders and
their positive efforts.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin made the remarks here today in a meeting
with Crown Prince Maha Vajiralongkorn of the Kingdom of
Thailand.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries get along with each other
sincerely and trust each other, adding that Sino-Thai
cooperation can be regarded as a fine example for mutually
beneficial cooperation between neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Jiang spoke highly of the positive contribution made by Thai
King Bhumibol Adulyadej and other Thai royal family members to the
growth of Sino-Thai friendship.
</P>
<P>
Jiang asked Vajiralongkorn to convey his greetings to the Thai
king and queen.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China sympathizes with and is concerned about
the financial crisis that occurred in Thailand last year, and has
offered whatever assistance it can.
</P>
<P>
He said that Thailand has a good economic basis and development
potential, and that its difficulties are temporary.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the Thai economy will be able to
get back on the track of sound development with concerted efforts
of the Thai people.
</P>
<P>
He recalled his own visit to Thailand, saying that Thailand's
economic achievements and its cultural relics had left a deep
impression on him.
</P>
<P>
Vajiralongkorn expressed his gratitude to the Chinese government
for inviting him to visit China again.
</P>
<P>
He said that this is his fourth visit to China, and that he has
visited many Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his admiration for the achievements China has made
over the past decade or so, and its splendid culture.
</P>
<P>
He said that Thai-Chinese relations are very good, and that
there are no problems that need to be resolved in the bilateral
relationship.
</P>
<P>
Thailand is prepared to further its cooperation with China, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Vajiralongkorn invited Jiang to visit Thailand on behalf of
the Thai king, for which Jiang expressed his gratitude. 
</P>
</TEXT>
