<HEADLINE> Surinam's President Concludes China Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Surinam's President Jules
Wijdenbosch wound up his state visit to China and left Shanghai
for a tour of China's famous scenic city of Hangzhou this evening.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Shanghai, Wijdenbosch met with Shanghai
Mayor Xu Kuangdi, in which both sides had a friendly conversation
on accelerating tangible cooperation between the city and Surinam.
</P>
<P>
He also visited the Pudong New Area here and conferred with
local businessmen on bilateral economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The president arrived here yesterday from south China's
Shenzhen city.  
</P>
