<HEADLINE> Quarry Collapse Kills 14 Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The collapse of the walls of a
stone quarry on May 18 killed 14 workers, injured 15 anothers and
left one missing in the suburbs of Qinzhou city, in south China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, a local official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The accident is under investigation by the local government,
the official said. In addition, all stone quarries in Qinzhou have
been ordered to suspend operations pending safety inspections.
</P>
<P>
At least 30 workers were buried by the collapse, witnesses said.
</P>
<P>
A local official led nearly 500 policemen, soldiers and medical
workers to rescue the victims as soon as the accident was reported.
</P>
<P>
Except for one worker suffering from a serious brain injury,
the other 14 injured are in stable condition, according to the public
security bureau chief of Qinzhou.
</P>
<P>
Local residents said that such stone quarries are mostly
privately run, and safety is often neglected.
</P>
<P>
The accident is possibly the worst of its kind ever in China,
an official with the region's labor department said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
