<HEADLINE> German Finance Minister Urges EU to Help Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 22 (Xinhua) -- German Finance Minister Theo Waigel
on Friday called on the European Union (EU) to act swiftly to help
the new Indonesian government launch economic and political
reforms.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a congress of his Christian Social Union (CSU)
party in the southern city of Ingolstadt, Waigel said Europe must
make all efforts to convince the new Indonesian president
B.J. Habibie of the need to carry out fundamental reforms.
</P>
