<HEADLINE> East China City to Promote Hi-tech Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Hi-tech industries, such as
electronic information, marine organism and medicine, have become a
driving force for the economic development in Qidong City in east
China's Jiangsu province.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the sales volume of 18 hi-tech firms made
up 12 percent of the city's total in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The city, located at the mouth of the Yangtze, is one of the
top 100 counties (cities) well-known in China for their rapid
development in science and technology.
</P>
<P>
So far, the city has put in 300 million yuan to develop 165
kinds of new products, including 40 state-level ones.
</P>
<P>
A batch of privately-owned hi-tech firms also emerged with the
support of local government. Shuangling Organic Products Co. Ltd,
a fodder producer, now can produce 2,000 tons of eel fodder
additives each year from crab shell, which accounts for one
fourth of the country's total. Their products have been sold well
to Japan, the United States, France and Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
