<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Development Bank Accelerates Loan Extension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The State Development Bank of China
(SDB), a major policy bank which funds key projects, has
accelerated its loan extension to help spur the country's economic
growth, bank figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
The SDB had approved loans valued at 30.1 billion yuan by
mid-May, a surge of 28 percent, with loans actually issued by then
hitting 27.2 billion yuan, up 15 percent year-on-year.
</P>
<P>
SDB President Chen Yuan said that the SDB's credit line this
year has been budgeted at 122.8 billion yuan, a rise of 11.68
percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
He said that loan priority will be given to railways, highways,
agriculture, forestry, water conservation, environmental
protection and other infrastructure projects, adding that the time
period for project evaluation will not exceed nine months for most
projects, and one year for particularly large projects.
</P>
<P>
The SDB conducted evaluation of 390 projects between January
and mid-May and completed 121 of them during the period, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
He also called for greater efforts to analyze and reduce
financial risks, and improve the quality of the bank's credit
assets.
</P>
<P>
In recent months many Chinese banks have decided to increase
loans to help ensure the successful realization of an
eight-percent increase in the national gross domestic product this
year.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that China's GDP grew 7.2 percent
year-on-year in the first quarter of this year, and 7.9 percent in
the January-April period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
