<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reports Drop in Chemical Fertilizer Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- China's total output of
agricultural-use nitrogenous, phosphate and potash fertilizers
stood at 6.74 million tons in the first quarter of this year, a
drop of 4.64 percent compared to the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
According to the State Statistics Bureau (SSB), Shandong,
Sichuan and Henan provinces had the highest output of chemical
fertilizers.
</P>
<P>
Shandong produced 647,100 tons of nitrogenous, phosphate and
potash fertilizers from January to March, down 2.38 percent;
Sichuan turned out 566,200 tons, up 5.5 percent; and Henan
produced 515,700 tons, down 7.41 percent.
</P>
<P>
The SSB reported that in March China produced 2.56 million tons
of chemical fertilizers, down 3.13 percent over the same period of
last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
