<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds Photographic Exhibition on Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A photographic exhibition featuring
the history and development of Macao opened today in the Museum of
the Chinese Revolution in Beijing, drawing a large number of
visitors.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the Xinhua News Agency head office and Xinhua
Macao Branch, the exhibition accounts for the origin of the Macao
question, the development of Macao and the procedure of its return
to the motherland, with more than 200 photos on display.
</P>
<P>
As the return of Macao is approaching, the Macao question has
become a hot topic for people in the inland areas. Most of the
visitors showed great interest on the region.
</P>
<P>
The Preparatory Committee for the Macao Special Administrative
Region was established in Beijing early this month, while a board
with a clock in countdown of Macao's return was set up in the
Tiananmen Square.  
</P>
