<HEADLINE> Inner Mongolia Forest Fire Doused </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A forest fire which had raged for
nine days in the Greater Xing'an Mountain Range in north China's
Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region was finally put out early this
morning, according to the local firefighting headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Now, firefighters are working to clear the burnt areas
and make sure that there is no resurgence of the fire.
</P>
<P>
At about six o'clock yesterday afternoon, the air force of the
People's Liberation Army succeeded in creating artificial rain. In
addition, drizzle fell on the entire fire-hit area, with moderate
rain in some places. As a result, the blaze was extinguished.
</P>
</TEXT>
