<HEADLINE> CPAFFC Seventh Council Meeting Closes in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Seventh Council meeting of the
Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries
(CPAFFC) closed here today.
</P>
<P>
Qi Huaiyuan was re-elected president of the CPAFFC.
</P>
<P>
During the 3-day meeting, participants discussed ways to
advance cooperation between the CPAFFC and foreign friendly
organizations and to develop good-neighborly relations between
China and its neighbors.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that the CPAFFC will serve as a bridge in promoting
economic and cultural cooperation between Chinese departments and
their foreign counterparts in addition to engaging in
people-to-people diplomacy.
</P>
<P>
The CPAFFC, founded in 1954, has made a major contribution to
the enhancement of understanding and friendship between the
peoples of China and the rest of the world, and to the promotion
of normalization of state-to-state relations between China and
foreign countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
