<DOCNO> XIE19980522.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Frenchmen Consider It Obligation to Learn First-Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 22 (Xinhua) -- 95 percent of the French people
consider it an obligation of citizens to learn first-aid
techniques in case some one needs emergency help, said a poll
published on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The poll, conducted by the CSA for the French Red Cross and
published by the daily Parisien, said that among 1,004 people
polled, 95 percent of them said schools should open lessons on
first-aid and 86 percent think that learning first-aid should be
compulsory for all.
</P>
<P>
Sixty-six percent of the people said that one should learn at
home a citizen's way of life in a community, while 53 percent said
that schools should also be the field to learn such things.
</P>
<P>
But most of the people said that the government, French
citizens, chiefs of enterprises, schools and trade unions have not
done enough to promote solidarity among citizens.
</P>
<P>
Humanitarian groups and charitable societies have just done
what they should, said half of the people polled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
