<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Broadly Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower across the board Friday as the
market succumbed to profit-taking ahead of the weekend, after
Thursday's sharp gains.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index fell 16.39
points to 577.23, the all-share Emas Index eased 4.13 points to
144.92, the Industrial Index dropped 22.30 points to 1,104.63 and
the second board index also dipped 11.65 points to 116.16.
</P>
<P>
Losers thumped gainers by 564 to 93, while 97 counters were
unchanged and 161 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's business shrunk to 131.179 million shares worth
278.955 million ringgit (about 73.602 million U.S. dollars) from
265.958 million shares valued at 517.837 million ringgit (about
136.632 million U.S. dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The main board's turnover sank to 113.497 million shares worth
254.580 million ringgit (about 67.171 million U.S. dollars) from
231.829 million shares valued at 470.631 million ringgit (about
124.177 million U.S. dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The second board's turnover fell to 17.682 million shares worth
24.955 million ringgit (about 6.584 million U.S. dollars) from
Thursday's 34.129 million shares valued at 47.205 million ringgit
(about 12.455 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market turnover ballooned to 50.999 million shares worth
63.606 million ringgit (about 16.782 million U.S. dollars) from
6.469 million shares valued at 7.731 million ringgit (about 2.039
million U.S. dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
An analyst said the rise Thursday was too sharp to be sustained
and the market was also closely looking at the developments in
Indonesia over the reform cabinet announced by newly appointed
President B.J. Habibie.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors sidelined awaiting clearer and further
details on the soon-to-be-established asset management company
announced by Deputy Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim on Wednesday, the
analyst said.
</P>
</TEXT>
