<HEADLINE> Indian Govt Uses Nuclear Tests to Divert People's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- an Indian public figure charged
the Indian BJP government for using the nuclear tests to divert
people's attention from the inability of the government to address
serious national problems.
</P>
<P>
In an article in the forthcoming issue of "People's Democracy",
 organ of the Communist Party of India (Marxism) (CPI-M), General
Secretary H. Singh Surjeet said, "Faced with problems of running a
shaky coalition and unable to address serious problems being faced
by the country, the BJP (Bharatiya Janata Party) is seeking to
divert attention of the people. The bomb has come as a handy
weapon to them."
</P>
<P>
"While the nation can take pride in indigenous development of
the nuclear technology, it is appalling that the country is being
asked to be in the forefront to take responsibility for the arms
race. It is only those wedded to communal and fascist philosophy
and ideology who can pursue this path," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Increased spending on armaments would lead to huge diversion
of funds from developmental activities," he further said.
</P>
<P>
"It is not the BJP but the country that will have to pay the
price for this reckless policy being pursued by the government. It
will deteriorate relations with our neighbors, lead to an arms
race in the subcontinent and consequent tensions, and
simultaneously mount increased burdens on the people," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Whatever be the cover, behind these tests lie the hidden
agenda of BJP - to advance the cause of Hinduism. The party is
adopting the very same methods that it adopted during the temple
agitation (in 1992)," Surjeet stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
