<HEADLINE> Macao, Guangdong Police to Increase Exchange of Information </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Police departments in Macao and
Guangdong province in south China will step up liaison and
exchange of information to maintain social order in the two
places.
</P>
<P>
Liaison police officers of Macao and Guangdong held a working
conference here Friday morning. A subsequent joint press release
said that the two sides will "continue to take the set measures to
expand liaison and exchange of information" between them.
</P>
<P>
The working conference is the eighth between the two sides,
aiming to decide the agenda for the upcoming 30th Guangdong-Macao
regular security meeting in Guangdong in July.
</P>
<P>
The two sides discussed a wide range of topics Friday,
including border patrol, exit and entry documents, and the
crackdown on cross-border illegal activities, especially organized
crimes.
</P>
<P>
Macao has been hit by a series of arson attacks and other
crimes over the past few weeks. Security issue has become the
number one concern of Macao residents, according to a recent poll.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
