<HEADLINE> Botswana Inflation Rises in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Botswana's year-on-year
inflation rate rose to 7.3 percent in April from 6.9 percent in
March, ending a deflationary trend in the past two years, the
country's central statistics office said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The rise marked an end of a 28-month downward trend in
inflation, when the rate steadily dropped from 10.8 percent in
December 1995 to 6.9 percent in March this year, South African
Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
The increase was largely attributed to price hikes in housing,
alcohol and tobacco, which accounted for 26 percent of the index
basket, the office said. 
</P>
