<HEADLINE> Blast Hits Telephone Exchange in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A bomb hit a telephone exchange in
the North-Central province of Sri Lanka Friday, damaging radio
communication equipment, police sources here said.
</P>
<P>
The blast at the telephone exchange in north Nochchiyagama town
did not cause casualties but many phones were affected, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate details of the blast, said the sources,
adding that investigation is on.
</P>
<P>
This is the third incident this month.
</P>
<P>
A similar bombing at telephone exchange in north-western
Kiliyapitiya took place on May 9. There were no casualties but
mobile phone communications in the area were disrupted.
</P>
<P>
Another telephone exchange at Ratnapura district, over 100
kilometers from Colombo, was attacked on May 16 with communication
equipment damaged. 
</P>
