<HEADLINE> Rate of Decline in Cyprus Stock Market Slows Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Stock Market this week
appeared to succumb to profit taking pressures, but kept
registering losses at a slower pace than the one experienced a
week ago.
</P>
<P>
According to the weekly market review prepared by the Cyprus
Investment and Securities Corporation Limited (CISCO), the CISCO
All-Share Index closed Thursday at 435.2 points, with daily
losses of 3.8 points and weekly losses of 9.5 points.
</P>
