<HEADLINE> China's Auto Production Remains Flat in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Statistics from the State Bureau
of Machine-building Industry show that 158,900 automobiles were
produced in April this year, down 0.06 percent from the same month
of last year.
</P>
<P>
The sales of automobiles increased by 2.13 percent over the
same period of last year to 158,000.
</P>
<P>
The statistics reveals that output and sales of heavy duty
cargo vehicles, middle-sized buses and cars increased
simultaneously in the month, while middle- and light-duty trucks
and light buses saw a decrease in both output and sales.
</P>
<P>
During the first four months of the year, output of automobiles
totaled 523,500, down 1.56 percent from the same period of last
year while sales of automobiles dropped by 0.23 percent to
513,500.  
</P>
</TEXT>
