<DOCNO> XIE19980522.0165 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Defense Minister Meets German Defense Force Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian, in a meeting today with Gen. Hartmut Bagger, inspector
general of the German Federal Defense Forces, criticised India for
conducting five nuclear tests recently and preaching "so-called
China threat theory".
</P>
<P>
He called the idea, which has been expressed by some Indians,
"totally groundless" and said that China will not change its
development direction and will continue to pursue an independent
foreign policy of peace.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that Japan recently made a movie that praises
Hideki Tojo, the military leader in the Second World War, and that
the Chinese people and other Asian people have strongly objected
to it.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who is also vice-chairman of the Central Military
Commission and state councillor, said that China places great
importance on relations with Germany, and that the Chinese
People's Liberation Army (PLA) is ready to increase friendly and
cooperative ties with the German armed forces.
</P>
<P>
He told Bagger that the two countries have common interests
instead of a fundamental conflict of interests.
</P>
<P>
Bagger said that India's nuclear tests are not conducive to
regional stability and could destabilize the situation in the
region and that Germany strongly condemned India's actions.
</P>
<P>
He said that his China visit has allowed him to see the
highly-disciplined and well-trained Chinese soldiers. He said that
he views his visit as a positive step in advancing relations
between the two armed forces.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
