<HEADLINE> Technology Zone For Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Lanzhou Technology Zone in
northwest China's Gansu Province had revenues of 1.45 billion yuan
and total output value of 1.29 billion yuan in 1997, up 51.8
percent and 53.8 percent from 1996, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The 5.4-square-kilometer zone got approval from the State
Council in 1991, and after seven years of development, has 501
enterprises, 250 of which are high-tech companies and 80 are
foreign-funded.
</P>
<P>
It has 237 non-state-owned enterprises and among them 21
enterprises have an annual revenue of at least ten million yuan
each, and three have an annual revenue of more than 100 million
yuan each.
</P>
<P>
A zone official says that it spent 1.28 billion yuan on
developing 1.59 square kilometers of land, finishing 455,900
square meters of construction, building a 4.9-km road, and
supplying water, heat, power, and communications.
</P>
<P>
The zone will develop pillar industries this year in fine
chemicals, bio-technology, energy-saving, environment protection,
and information technology to ensure two billion yuan in revenue
and an output value of 1.7 billion yuan and profits of 254 million
yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
