<HEADLINE> Steady Growth in China's Transport Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- According to China's State
Statistics Bureau, the volume of goods transported in the first
quarter was down marginally, but the number of passengers was up
somewhat.
</P>
<P>
The transport industry carried 603 million tons, a year-on-year
drop of 6.3 percent, except for air transport, which carried
303,200 tons, up 9 percent. There were 1.3 billion passengers, an
increase of 5.2 percent, but water and air transport were down 9.2
percent and 0.3 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The major harbors handled 200 million tons of goods during the
period, a drop of 2.7 percent, while the post and
telecommunications sector did 51.5 billion yuan in business, an
increase of 37.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
