<HEADLINE> KKSB, Citibank Join Local ATM Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai branches of Hong Kong
and Shanghai Banking Corporation (HKSB) and the Citibank of the
United States have been selected as the first two overseas banks
to join the city's ATM system, according to the Shanghai Branch of
the People's Bank of China, the central bank,
</P>
<P>
The move means that holders of credit cards issued by the two
overseas banks can draw Renminbi yuan from more than 500 ATMs
installed here by the local banks such as the Industrial and
Commercial Bank, the Bank of Communications, and the Shanghai
Pudong Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the decision, Shanghai's credit card network has been
electronically linked with those of Visa International and
MasterCard Group. The local credit card network currently has
access to more than 2,600 banks in more than 200 countries and
regions.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the participation of the HKSB and Citibank in
the local ATM network will significantly strengthen the link
between Shanghai and the international credit card market. HKSB
and Citibank are two of the nine overseas banks authorized to deal in
local currency business in the Pudong New Area on a trial basis.
</P>
</TEXT>
