<HEADLINE> Fujian Development Zone Attracts Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A state-level development zone in
east China's Fujian province has become a hot spot for overseas
investment, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
More than 260 overseas-funded projects have been set up in the
Fuqing Rongqiao Economic and Technological Development Zone, which
was founded in September 1987 and approved by the State Council as
a state-level development zone in October 1992, with the total
investment hitting 1.51 billion US dollars. The enterprises have
an average overseas investment of 5.58 million US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
Investors in the zone, which is about 50 km away from Fuzhou,
the provincial capital, come from a dozen countries and regions
including Singapore, Malaysia, Indonesia, the Republic of Korea,
Japan, Germany, France, the United States, Australia, Taiwan, Hong
Kong, and Macao.
</P>
<P>
Currently, 130 of the overseas-funded enterprises have begun
operation and their combined output value and export volume have
reached 34 billion yuan (about four billion US dollars) and 3.2
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
In another analysis, overseas-funded enterprises in the zone
cover such sectors as electronics, chemical fibre, plastics, auto
parts, garment, foodstuffs and aluminium. Their products are sold
mainly to Southeast Asia, Europe and Americas.
</P>
<P>
Fuqing is a native place of many overseas Chinese.  
</P>
</TEXT>
