<HEADLINE> High-tech Corridor Takes Shape in Shanghai's Pudong Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A high-tech industrial corridor
has been basically formed in Shanghai's Pudong New Area, a rising
finance and trade zone.
</P>
<P>
The corridor area, which has an annual output value of more
than 50 billion yuan, covers four high-tech zones: the Waigaoqiao
Free Trade Zone, the Jinqiao Modern Technology Park, the
Zhangjiang High-tech Area, and the Sunqiao Modern Agriculture
Development Zone.
</P>
<P>
Over 100 world-renowned high-tech enterprises and even more
small high-tech firms have shown up in the corridor, with the most
famous including Intel, Hewlett Packard, At&AMP;T, IBM, Ricoh Company,
Hitachi Company, and Siemens.
</P>
<P>
Experts have agreed that the high-tech corridor has a great
growth potential and its influence will expand further as more
projects there open for business.
</P>
<P>
Many multinational corporations have expressed interest in
investing in the high-tech corridor, with more than a dozen having
agreeed to either invest or increase investment so far this year.
</P>
<P>
Pudong, which is separated from the city proper by the Huangpu
River, was just farm fields until it was made a special economic
zone by the Chinese government in April 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
