<HEADLINE> Gansu Province Steps up Technological Upgrading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
will spend seven billion yuan this year on technological
improvements, especially in pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
A provincial government official says that this old industrial
center has encountered certain difficulties like outmoded
equipment and technology, and a diminished competitiveness in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
To change this, the province will put 40 billion yuan in the
1996-2000 period into technological improvements in 387 projects.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, Gansu spent 11.48 billion yuan on
technological upgrading in 74 projects.
</P>
<P>
According to this year's technological improvement plan, Gansu
will have 135 projects, 5 of which are key projects. The province
is also including non-state-owned enterprises in its technological
improvement plan. 
