<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Reports Fast Growth in Telecommunications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The telecommunications sector of
east China's Jiangsu Province has experienced fast growth in
recent years, according to official figures.
</P>
<P>
The size of Jiangsu's telecommunications network, consisting of
telephones, mobile phones, digital communications and multi-media
communication, is the second largest in China, next only to that
of Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Jiangsu has 6.53 million telephone users and 1.08
million mobile phone subscribers, or 15.5 telephones per 100
people.
</P>
<P>
As the telecommunications network expands, people in Jiangsu
now can dial to more than 180 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu's first telephone was installed in the city of Suzhou
in 1898.  
</P>
