<HEADLINE> Northern Chinese Aquarium's Underwater Walkway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Red Coral Aquarium
Technology Development Co. Ltd. of Shanghai is building a 49-meter
underwater walkway that zigzags through the Shanhaiguan Aquarium
in north China's Hebei Province to give visitors a closer look at
marine life.
</P>
<P>
The construction project is the first of its kind in China
using Chinese technology, funding, and materials. Pressurization
and lighting have passed the requisite tests after being made in
line with international standards.
</P>
<P>
The project would cost more than one million yuan (120,000 US
dollars), in contrast with a cost of from 10 million (1.2 million
US dollars) to 100 million yuan (12 million US dollars) if the
technology and materials were imported. 
</P>
