<HEADLINE> China Looking For Ways To Protect Marine Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- China's highest legislative body
will start a large-scale campaign to increase awareness of the
need to protect the marine environment and develop the seas, a
spokesman said recently.
</P>
<P>
The National People's Congress' Environmental and Resources
Protection Committee will sponsor a tour by the media of coastal
areas, for World Marine Year.
</P>
<P>
The government and the NPC have answered a call by the United
Nations to protect marine resources better for sustained economic
development, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
China has 18,000 kilometers of coastline and more than 6,500
islands and has jurisdiction over nearly three million square
kilometers of ocean.
</P>
<P>
The value of marine production in China has grown 22.2 percent
annually in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The tour will visit 11 provinces, municipalities, and
autonomous regions. 
</P>
