<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, May 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India's opposition parties and noted figures have
accused Home Minister L. K. Advani of creating war hysteria
against Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Advani in his recent strong worded statements linked India's
nuclear capability with the Kashmir issue and threatened to go
pro-active against Pakistan "misadventures."
</P>
<P>
"They are trying for an escalation of tension with the
neighbors," The Hindustan Times quoted Congress leader Ms. Ambica
Soni as saying here Friday.(India-Opposition-Home Minister)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton on Thursday urged
voters in Ireland and Northern Ireland to vote "yes" on an
historic peace deal and "embrace a common future in peace."
</P>
<P>
Clinton made the call in a White House ceremony to sign the
U.S. ratification of the NATO expansion to include Poland, Hungary
and the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
"I'd like to put in one last plug for the vote in Ireland and
Northern Ireland tomorrow," Clinton said. (Clinton-Ireland-Peace)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- A passenger airplane of Bosnian airlines Thursday
landed on the Belgrade airport, marking the resumption of air
services between Sarajevo and Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
This was the first airliner to have arrived in Belgrade from
Sarajevo since the disintegration of the former Yugoslavia in 1992
which was followed by the Bosnia-Herzegovina civil war. The war
ended at the end of 1995. (Yugoslavia-Bosnia-Airlines)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. Justice Department Thursday rejected a
proposed alliance between American Airlines and British Airways.
</P>
<P>
The two giants alliance could win the green light if the United
States and Britain eliminate government-imposed restrictions on
flights and prices between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Other airlines also should be given enough takeoff and landing
slots to run 24 additional daily round trips between London's
Heathrow Airport and cities in the United States, the department
said. (US-Britain-Airlines)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesian President B.J. Habibie announced here
Friday the formation of his 36-member new cabinet, in which most
of the important posts are taken by old ministers.
</P>
<P>
Revealing the cabinet list at the President Palace, the
president said the lineup, formed within 24 hours after he assumed
office, will break from corruption, nepotism and monopoly.
</P>
<P>
The new government will do its best to carry out total reforms
in the country in bid to overcome economic crisis, he
added. (Indonesia-New Cabinet)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Georgia will arrange for refugees to return to the
breakaway region of Abkhazia through talks and other means,
Georgian President Eduard Shevardnadze said Thursday in Tbilisi,
capital of Georgia.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said Shevardnadze made the remarks at the
country's Security Commission meeting held on the worsening
situation in the Gali region.
</P>
<P>
No matter what objection the Abkhaz separatists took, Georgia
would restore its territorial integrity, Shevardnadze said. The
refugees would certainly return to
Abkhazia. (Georgia-Abkhazia-Refugees) 
</P>
