<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Make 1,000 Commercial Firms Private </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- China's leading metropolis of
Shanghai has decided to turn 1,000 small state or collective
commercial businesses into private or partnership entities in
three years, according to Ling Kongshan, deputy director of the
city's Commercial Committee.
</P>
<P>
Official registration with the industrial and commercial
administrations by partnership entities has started this week.
</P>
<P>
The commercial companies to change hand have posted either
long-term losses or marginal profits or assets with a value
smaller than that of liabilities, Ling said.
</P>
<P>
He added that eligible buyers are managers and groups of
workers who have worked in the original firms or the same sector,
and the transformation process will be conducted through public
bidding.
</P>
<P>
Altogether, Shanghai has 5,500 small and medium-sized
commercial businesses, 180 of which have already been turned into
private owership.
</P>
<P>
Ling said that this is an important part of Shanghai's effort
to reform its commercial sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
