<HEADLINE> Jiangsu-Taiwan Economic Ties Expanding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Economic exchanges between east
China's Jiangsu province and Taiwan have expanded greatly in
recent years, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
The import and export volume between Jiangsu and Taiwan totaled
1.41 billion US dollars between 1991 and 1995, with the growth
rate averaging 146 percent a year. The bilateral trade volume grew
another 27.9 percent annually to 2.31 billion US dollars during
the 1996-1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu had approved more than 7,200 enterprises funded by
Taiwan companies by the end of last year, with contracted and
paid-in investment from Taiwan hitting 11.2 billion and five
billion US dollars, respectively.
</P>
<P>
In another analysis, 39 of Taiwan's largest 100 private
companies have made investment in Jiangsu, one of the economic
powerhouses in the country.
</P>
<P>
While more Taiwan companies invest in Jiangsu, the average size
of Taiwan investment in each project has also expanded, from 1.02
million US dollars for the 1990 -1996 period to more than two
million US dollars for 1997.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu's Taiwan-funded enterprises, which are mainly
concentrated in Suzhou, Wuxi and other southern cities, cover
energy, transportation, raw materials and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Currently, more Taiwan companies have expressed interest in
investing in Jiangsu, according to an official source. 
</P>
</TEXT>
