<HEADLINE> Injured Rare Bird Taken Good Care of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- An injured Black stork, rescued by
two villagers in northwest China's Qinghai Province, has been
taken good care of at the Xining Zoo.
</P>
<P>
While walking in the woods in mid-April, Xing Xiangui and Liu
Cunzhong, farmers from Ping'an County, happened to find the bird,
which could not fly because of a bullet wound in its wing. They
took it home and took good care of it.
</P>
<P>
They finally got in touch with the Xining Zoo, which sent
experts to help identify the bird.
</P>
<P>
According to experts, the bird is a black stork, a rare bird
under first-class state protection.
</P>
<P>
They concluded that the bird had got lost after being injured
by a shot. 
</P>
