<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM Calls for Diversified Use of Jute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina on Thursday stressed the importance of diversified and
increased commercial use of jute for the country's economic
development, the independent United News of Bangladesh (UNB)
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The commercial use of jute should be increased and markets
expanded," she said this while meeting with members of the
Parliamentary Standing Committee on the Jute Ministry here.
</P>
<P>
In the wake of environment concern, the use of jute should be
increased in the world market and Bangladesh could capture the
market by innovating diversified use of jute, she emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh is the biggest jute-exporting country in the world
and occupies 58 percent of the global jute market.
</P>
<P>
Of the country's annual production of over 5 million bales
(about 0.9 million tons), 90 percent is exported to some 20
countries.
</P>
<P>
The jute industry is the country's second major foreign
exchange earner after the ready-made garment industry. It earned
about 139 million U.S. dollars from exporting jute goods in the
July 1996-June 1997 fiscal year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
