<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Forestry Development in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved Thursday
a loan and a credit totaling 200 million U.S. dollars to support
forestry development in poor Chinese areas.
</P>
<P>
The financing includes an interest-free credit of 100 million
dollars and a 100-million-dollar loan.
</P>
<P>
Aiming to reduce poverty, develop forestry and manage the
environment, the project will develop forest resources in poor
areas in central and western China on a sustainable and
participatory basis .
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to increase the per capita income of
about two million poor people above the poverty line when the
project is completed.
</P>
<P>
A considerable number of job opportunities will also be created
under to the project.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be provided by the International Development
Association, the World Bank's concessional lending arm for
developing countries. 
