<HEADLINE> Hot Weather Hits Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A hot and humid weather has been
hitting Bangladesh these days, making many people here suffer
headstroke.
</P>
<P>
Dhaka, capital of this South Asian country, experienced the
hottest and most humid day Thursday with the temperature soaring
to 37.5 degree Celsius, the highest in May in 28 years, press
reports said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The mercury on Thursday hit season's new high, 41.8 degree
Celsius, recorded at Rajshahi district, 204 km northwest of here,
and it might climb a bit further, according to experts here.
</P>
<P>
Two laborers died of sunstroke and 18 others fell sick in the
northwest district of Pabna in the past few days.
</P>
<P>
"The temperature could rise by 1-2 degrees until rain comes in
a few days," a senior meteorologist was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The hot weather was due to a "heat low" in Bangladesh and
adjoining West Bengal of India and "above normal" humidity, he
explained.
</P>
<P>
The southern part of the country was already having pre-monsoon
rain and the whole country was expected to have it within the next
three to four days, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
