<HEADLINE> Indonesian Cabinet Lineup Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President B.J. Habibie
announced here Friday the formation of his 36-member new cabinet,
in which most of the important posts are taken by old ministers.
</P>
<P>
Revealing the cabinet list at the President Palace, the
president said the lineup, formed within 24 hours after he assumed
office, will break from corruption, nepotism and monopoly.
</P>
<P>
The new government will do its best to carry out total reforms
in the country in bid to overcome economic crisis, he added.
</P>
<P>
The four coordinating ministers from the new cabinet are still
the old ones. They are Coordinating Minister for Defense and
Security Feisal Tanjung, Coordinating Minister for economy,
Finance and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita, Coordinating Minister
for Development Supervisory and State Administrative Reform
Hartarto Kartasasmita and Coordinating Minister for People's
Welfare and Poverty Alleviation/Chairman of Family Coordinating
Board Haryono Suyono.
</P>
<P>
The Home Affairs portfolio was changed from R. Hartono to
Syaruwan Hamid, former deputy House Speaker from Armed Forces
Faction.
</P>
