<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, May 21 (Xinhua) -- China attaches great importance to
its relations with Spain and is ready to raise friendly ties to a
new level, Li Ruihuan, Chairman of the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Conference (CPPCC), said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with Spanish Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar, Li
said relations between the two countries have developed smoothly
in the economic, trade, cultural, scientific and technological
fields since they forged diplomatic ties 25 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leader stressed that China would uphold and enlarge
its policies of opening to the outside world and participate in
international cooperation in all fields.
</P>
<P>
He said China hoped that the developed countries and world
economic and trade organizations would open their door wider to
China, and give the fair treatment to China that it deserves.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the international community should quicken the
steps in building a new world economic order, which is fair,
reasonable, equal and mutually beneficial.
</P>
<P>
A significant and profound change in today's world, Li said,
is that resolving international disputes through discussion and
dialogue has become the common understanding and demand of more
and more nations.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish prime minister said Spain had always supported and
understood China, and it would continue to do so in the future.
</P>
<P>
Aznar said he was looking forward to visiting China this
November and believed his visit would be successful.
</P>
<P>
He said high level exchanges between the two countries would
promote the development of the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Li, who arrived here Thursday afternoon for a four-day official
goodwill visit, is expected to meet Spanish King Juan Carlos I and
Senate Chairman Juan Ignacio Barrero on Friday. 
