<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Financial Sector Does Well in Guangdong in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- All indicators show that the
financial sector of south China's Guangdong Province was operating
on a sound track in the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of March, the bank deposits outstanding stood at
1,150 billion yuan (138.55 billion US dollars) in Guangdong, an
increase of about 34 billion yuan from the beginning of the
year. Among the amount, there were 49 billion yuan of new savings
deposits. a rise of 7.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The loans outstanding amounted to 835.5 billion yuan by the end
of March, or 15 billion yuan more than early January, with loans
to rural enterprises, ventures involving overseas investment, and
the private sector rising by a large margin.
</P>
<P>
Though the supply of cash dropped sharply to 756 million yuan
as compared with over 15.1 billion yuan in the same period of last
year, the speed of withdrawing money from circulation accelerated,
with the rate reaching 98.37 percent in March.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's gross domestic product (GDP) in the first quarter
reached 101.3 billion yuan, a year-on-year rise of 8.2 percent,
which was the lowest growth rate recorded since 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
