<HEADLINE> 4 Key Tamil Rebel Activists Arrested in Sri Lankan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police have arrested
four key Tamil rebel activists in connection with the bombing of
the five-star Galadhari Hotel in Colombo last October and a series
of attacks on military targets, police sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
All the four men are described as hard-core members of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) who have been fighting a
15-year war against government troops for a separate state in the
north and east of the country.
</P>
<P>
The four rebel cadres had been given special training for their
sabotage work in a camp in Batticaloa in the East of the country,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
In addition to these four suspects, seven others had been
reportedly arrested earlier. They have all been remanded pending
further investigations. 
</P>
