<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Grows in Hunan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Investment from overseas grew in
central-south China's Hunan Province during the first quarter of
this year.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that Hunan, which is a major haven for
overseas funding in central and western China, has, during the
three-month period, approved 79 projects involving direct overseas
investment in the first quarter, a year-on-year rise of 11 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, contracts were signed on the use of over 200 million
US dollar of direct overseas investment, a jump of 46 percent over
the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Also in the first quarter, the exports by the Sino-overseas
joint ventures and solely-overseas-funded firms amounted to 82.51
million US dollars, an increase of 22 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, the amount of previously pledged overseas investment
put into place in the first quarter dropped by 19 percent to stand
at 134 million US dollars. The decline was caused mainly by delays
from southeast Asian countries, Japan and the Republic of Korea
(ROK), provincial officials said.
</P>
<P>
Provincial experts called for enhanced efforts to guarantee the
inflow of overseas investment in the second quarter, which is
regarded as a peak season for the arrival of foreign investment.
</P>
</TEXT>
