<HEADLINE> Shops Check on Escalator Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Shopping marts in Beijing are
carrying out safety checks on their escalators, following a
series of accidents in which two boys died and a girl was
seriously injured, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Labor Bureau has asked enterprises and shops to follow
strictly the guidelines on self-checking for escalator safety
issued by the former Ministry of Labor.
</P>
<P>
They cover the safety of the escalators themselves and safety
requirements at entrances and exits.
</P>
<P>
Escalators with severe safety problems must be shut down until
they are required, the labor bureau said.
</P>
<P>
District labor bureaux are urged to carry out random
inspections on the self-checks. They should hand in the results
before June 10.
</P>
<P>
There have been three accidents since January at Xinxing Xidan
Shopping Centre in Majiapu Residential Area in Fengtai
District. Two three-year-old boys died after falling from the
junction between two flights of escalators and one girl was
severely injured when she was crushed by an escalator.
</P>
<P>
At present, Beijing has more than 2,000 escalators.  
</P>
</TEXT>
