<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Turkey to Sign Free Trade Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine and Turkey are to sign a free
trade treaty in the near future, Ukraine Presidential press
secretary Alexandr Maidannik announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
President Leonid Kuchma and visiting Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel also discussed expanding cooperation in military and
security fields, according to Maidannik.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents exchanged views on Ukraine's involvement in
transporting Caspian oil to Europe, the press secretary said.
</P>
<P>
During Demirel's three-day visit, the two Black Sea countries
have signed a series of inter-governmental agreements in the
health, environmental and financial fields. The two countries also
signed a consular agreement.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the trade volume between Ukraine and Turkey amounted
to 900 million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
