<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Farmers in Mountain Areas Prospering by Moving Elsewhere </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in Daba Mountains of
southwest China's Chongqing Municipality have considerably
improved their life by moving elsewhere.
</P>
<P>
In Chengkou County, for example, some 700 households of more
than 3,000 people, who used to live in mountain areas with an
elevation of over 1,500 meters, have come down and resettled along
roadsides and river valley areas.
</P>
<P>
Newly-erected buildings and cement highways are posing a
striking contrast with thatched sheds and rugged roads in the
mountains.
</P>
<P>
The county government started the resettlement project in 1996,
ruling that resettled farmers can do breeding and other business,
and at the same time manage their farmland and forests in the
mountains.
</P>
<P>
Farmer Yuan Shenglin in Beiping Township has repaid the loans
for his new house by opening a barber's shop and farming on
contracted land.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that almost every resettled family now earns
more than 5,000 yuan on average. And mom and pop shops, catering
and entertainment services in newly emerging small towns are
contributing increasingly to the local economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
