<HEADLINE> Conservative Leads in Colombian Election Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Conservative candidate
Andres Pastrana Arango gained 41.7 percent of votes in a poll
conducted by the Napoleon Franco polling firm, 10 days before the
Colombian presidential elections.
</P>
<P>
Liberal Party candidate Horacio Serpa Uribe got 24 percent of
the straw votes, 17 points behind the conservative candidate,
according to the poll which has a margin of 2.6 percent error.
</P>
<P>
Option Life candidate Noemi Sanin de Rubio was six points
behind the Liberal Party candidate, with 17.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The canvassing was done on May 14-18, with a sample of 1,419
people in Bogota, Cali, Medellin and 12 other cities. 
