<HEADLINE> Austria Welcomes Resignation of President Suharto </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Chancellor Vikto Klima
Thursday expressed appreciation for the resignation of Indonesian
President Suharto, hoping it would calm riot-torn Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
On a visit to Tunisia, Klima said Indonesia was a politically
and economically important nation due to its large population of
200 million, adding that Austria welcomed all moves conducive to
stability in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Suharto, beset by turmoil and threatened with impeachment,
decided to quit his job on Thursday after three decades in power
and handed over power to Vice-President Jusuf Habibie.
</P>
<P>
Austria's Vice-Chancellor and Foreign Minister Wolfgang
Schuessel said Suharto has made a brave decision.
</P>
<P>
The resignation, which is expected to help restore order in
Indonesia, will give the new leadership opportunities to carry out
profound political and economic reforms, Schuessel said. 
</P>
