<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Communist Party Founder Passes Away </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Professor Juan Bautista Fuenmayor,
considered one of the most brilliant Venezuelans of this century
and founder of the Venezuelan Communist Party, passed away
Wednesday at 93, the "O Globo" newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Fuenmayor, also former Santa Maria University president, was
born in the city of Maracaibo, in the Zulia state, on September
28, 1905.
</P>
<P>
In 1921, he went to Caracas to finish his bachelorship and to
start law studies in the former University of San Francisco, the
precursor of the Central University of Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
Fuenmayor was the winner of the "Francisco Gonzalez Ginan"
History Award and a professor in the subject matters of Law
Philosophy, Political Economy, and Constitutional Law. He
consecrated his life to the struggle for social justice.
</P>
<P>
He is also the author of an ample literary work that includes a
great variety of titles.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan Communist Party was founded by Fuenmayor, which
was declared a legal party in 1945, but in 1950 the authorities
outlawed it when it called oil workers to strike. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
