<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Harmoko: Indonesian Parliament to Watch Habibie's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's House Speaker Harmoko
said the House would closely watch the policies of newly-appointed
President B.J. Habibie in solving the urgent problems facing the
country.
</P>
<P>
"The House will assess the president's policies and monitor
their implementation," Harmoko said here Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
The House's attention would cover the government's policies in
solving the prolonged economic crisis and in implementing the Main
Guidelines of State Policies (GBHN), official Antara News Agency
Friday quoted Harmoko as saying.
</P>
<P>
Habibie assumed the presidential office Thursday morning soon
after Soeharto announced his resignation.
</P>
<P>
Harmoko said one of the priority tasks of the new national
leadership should reform various aspects of the people's life.
</P>
<P>
"Reformation must not be allowed to stop if we want to
anticipate further developments in various fields of life," he
noted.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on Soeharto's decision to appoint Vice President BJ
Habibie as the new president, Harmoko said the step was in
accordance with article 8 of Indonesia's 1945 Constitution.
</P>
<P>
The article states: "In the event of the sudden demise or
incapacitation of the president, or should he be unable to execute
his duties during his term of office, the presidency shall be
assumed by the Vice President until the expiry of that term."
</P>
</TEXT>
