<HEADLINE> Makinen On Course of Winning Third Consecutive Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, May 21 (Xinhua) -- World champion Tommi Makinen
is on the course of winning his third successive Rally of
Argentina when he finished the first leg ahed of Didier Auriol of
France on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Driving a Mitsubishi, Makinen began the day just over one
second behind the leader Colin McRae after Wednesday's stage.
</P>
<P>
Makinen finished no lower than third in any of the eight stages
on Thursday, completed the first leg in one hour 32 minutes and
58.7 seconds, 12.4 seconds ahead of Auriol.
</P>
<P>
Auriol held a 2.5-second lead over world championship leader
McRae who finished the day in third place.
</P>
<P>
The drivers face a further eight stages on Friday with the
rally due to finish in Cordoba on Saturday afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
