<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, May 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The U.N. Security Council Thursday
unanimously adopted a resolution authorizing an increase of 30
posts in the strength of the International Police Task Force
(IPTF) stationed in Bosnia and Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council made the decision after it reviewed the
U.N. secretary-general's latest report on the developments in the
area. (UN-IPTF-Bosnia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton Thursday gave formal
U.S. approval for expanding the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO) to include Poland, Hungary and the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
At a White House ceremony, Clinton signed the instrument of
ratification passed by the Senate on April 30.
</P>
<P>
"Our goal is to help to build a Europe that is undivided, free,
democratic, at peace and secure," Clinton said before putting his
signature to the document. (US-NATO-Clinton)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- At least one person was killed and 24 others were
wounded when a student opened fire with a rifle in a high school
cafeteria in Springfield, Oregon, Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The gunfire, the latest in a series of school shootings across
the country, began just before classes started at 8:00 a.m. in the
Thurston High School cafeteria. Among the wounded, seven were in
critical conditions. (US-School-Shooting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- The parliament of Moldova validated on Thursday
the new cabinet led by Ion Ciubuc and it's work program, reported
the Messenger, the Moldovan National TV Station.
</P>
<P>
Thursday was the deadline, according to the constitution, when
the premier designated had to ask a confidence vote to his
team. (Moldova-New Cabinet)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States will see whether proper
conditions are created in Indonesia for Washington to support a
resumption of disbursements to Indonesia under a 43 billion
U.S. dollars International Monetary Fund rescue package, The State
Department said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
James Rubin, the State Department spokesman, told reporters
that the United States wants to see a series of principles to be
followed by Indonesia's new leader Jusuf Habibie before it could
consider the possibility of resumption of IMF aid to
Indonesia. (US-Indonesia-Aid)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- About 50,000 people who had fled to bushes and
volcano forests, or to the Democratic Republic of Congo in the
past months are massively returning to their homes in the
prefectures of Gisenyi and Ruhengeri, Rwanda News Agency (RNA)
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The movement started about a month ago," the assistant
prefect in charge of administrative affairs in Gisenyi, northwest
Rwanda, Gerard Ngoga indicated. "With this week alone, we have in
some communes registered up to 2,000 displaced people flocking out
of hideouts everyday." (Rwanda-Villagers)  
</P>
