<HEADLINE> Stocks Fall in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street fell
Thursday as the Dow Jones industrial average dropped 39.11 points
to 9,132.37.
</P>
<P>
Broader indexes also retreated despite some sharp gains in
Asian markets following the latest developments in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Shares of big-name technology companies suffered again on
Thursday. Last week, Hewlett-Packard and National Semiconductor
both warned of weak profits.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 fell 4.42 to 1,114.64, and the
technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index fell 10.76 to 1,820.99.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 7-to-6 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 551.97 million
shares, down from Wednesday's 597.29 million.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index fell 1.73 to 576.90, and the American
Stock Exchange composite index rose 0.14 to 732.36.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 1.34 to
467.20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
