<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Dollar Falls Against yen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar fell broadly here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In late New York trading, the dollar was quoted at 134.78 yen,
down from 135.98 late Wednesday. The dollar also was changing
hands at 1.7558 German marks, down from 1.7698.
</P>
<P>
The dollar had benefited from a flow of funds into the United
States as economic and political unrest in Indonesia spelled more
international investors to change their money into the U.S.
dollar.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few weeks, Japan's currency suffered because of
its economic ties to Indonesia. On Tuesday, the dollar rose to
136.44 yen, its highest level against the Japanese currency since
August 1991.
</P>
<P>
The resignation Thursday of President Suharto of Indonesia
prompted investors to buy yen, and raise cash for doing so by
selling dollars,
</P>
<P>
Other late dollar rates in New York, compared with late
Wednesday: 1.4618 Swiss francs, down from 1.4758; 5.8860 French
francs, down from 5.9340; 1,732.05 Italian lire, down from
1,744.00; and 1.4495 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4493.
</P>
<P>
The British pound was quoted at 1.6327 U.S. dollars, up from
1.6324 U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
