<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopian PM Urges Public to Follow Govt's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles
Zenawi urged Thursday the Ethiopian people to adhere to and
implement the decisions of the government on the sovereignty of
the country.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference to Ethiopian journalists in connection
with Ethio-Eritrean border disputes, Meles said peace is "our
priority" to which end the government is striving but it will be
obliged to defend the nation's sovereignty if peace efforts are
in a deadlock.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted Meles as saying that the
government is doing everything in its capacity to integrate and
uphold these two principles to resolve the disputes with Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
He said that Ethiopia is ready to go to any length in defusing
disputes in peace but will never bow to impositions by the use of
force.
</P>
<P>
Meles said that Ethiopia is committed to the promotion of
peace because its priority is development, alleviation of poverty
and backwardness and he stressed the determination of the
government to fully exploit the valueless peaceful times to this
end.
</P>
<P>
The Eritrean government has committed a grave historical
blunder in resorting to the use of force to resolve the dispute,
Meles said, adding that unless the use of force as a means to
resolve territorial claims is totally abandoned, it will gravely
endanger the peace in the sub-region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
